description: Building the Worlds Most Luxurious Cruise Ship Travel Documentary hosted by Julian Barret, published by Channel 5 in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/e/ed/Building-the-Worlds-Most-Luxurious-Cruise-Ship-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Building The Worlds Most Luxurious Cruise Ship Documentary following engineers and designers as they construct the liner Seven Seas Explorer. The aim of cruise boss Frank Del Rio is to make it the most luxurious ship of its type, designed to convey 750 passengers when others of its size would hold 5,000. 1) 1 Part one of two. Building the £360million vessel is a race against time for Italian shipbuilders Fincantieri, as tickets for the maiden voyage go on sale long before it is finished. The most expensive suite boasts a grand piano, a butler and its own spa, and costs £8,000 per night, while the owner is spending £5million on art works to furnish the rooms.
